EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO BUSINESSES AND PROFESSIONS -- THE PRIMARY CARE
PRESERVATION ACT
***
1 This act would authorize a physician practice to charge a practice support contribution;
2 provided that, the amount charged does not exceed one hundred twenty dollars ($120) per year, per
3 patient, enrolled in a healthcare insurance plan, (excluding Medicaid and traditional Medicare).
4 Patients in arrears would still be entitled to receive standard and customary care, including
5 medication refills for thirty (30) days and medical record transfers.
6 This act would take effect upon passage.
